    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-13T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-13T18:00:00-05:00" n="352"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d352">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/407</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-13T19:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 13, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8222. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 652. Referring further Embassy’s 10364, May 31, 3 p.m., your 690.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d352fn2">Not printed; see the foregoing telegram.</note> The
                    following note was delivered to the Swedish Minister by the Department on June
                    10: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Referring to our conversation of Thursday morning and in order that there
                            can be no further misunderstanding on the subject of the shipping
                            agreement, I beg to say that the War Trade Board does not insist on the
                            four months’ charter of the replacing vessel which <pb facs="0441"
                                n="1275" xml:id="pg_1275"/> come from Sweden under the <hi
                                rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi>. The Board merely insists that the
                            replacing ships shall leave coincidentally with, or prior to, the
                            departure from the United States for Sweden of the boats operating under
                            the <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi.</hi>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
